            <table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="2">
              <tr> 
                <td class="chblue"><font class="h1font"> Advanced Decks</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr><td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="3"><tr><td><font class="bfont"><table width="100%" border="0" cellpadding="4" cellspacing="0"><tr><td colspan="2"><font class="h1font">Shadow falls over Naroom</font></td></tr><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Rating</Font></TD><TD><table width='74' border='0' cellspacing='0' cellpadding='0'><tr><td background='/magination/gfx/5star.gif'><img src='/lotr/gfx/trans.gif' width='1' height='25'></td></tr></table><font size=1>(3.7)</font> | <A HREF="/magination/decks/decks.php?reviews=32849&PHPSESSID=6b84db03bbbbdaba0e935e0d072b04f6">Read Reviews</A></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Author</font></TD><TD><font class="bfont"> <A HREF="http://www.decktech.net/magination/main/mpage.php?member=17602">Travis "Dark_Twins" Dutra</A></FONT> <font class="afont"> <a href='http://www.decktech.net/magination/main/mpage.php?member=17602&sub=1'> (Subscribe to this member)</a></font></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Description</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> No one can handle the Dark Twins. Powerfull relics, and spells, with a little bit of naroom added in.</FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Submitted</Font></TD><TD><font class="bfont"> June 19, 2004</FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Cards</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> Magi~<br />
<br />
The Dark Twins<br />
Starting:Any one core spell, any one core creature, <a href="javascript:card_browser(555)">Entomb</a><br />
<br />
<a href="javascript:card_browser(575)">Warrada</a><br />
Starting: <a href="javascript:card_browser(582)">Chaos Jile</a>, Tomes of the Great Library, <a href="javascript:card_browser(575)">Warrada</a>&#39;s Ring<br />
<br />
<br />
Creatures~<br />
Rabid <a href="javascript:card_browser(607)">Wasperine</a> x3<br />
<a href="javascript:card_browser(582)">Chaos Jile</a> x2<br />
Dagok x3<br />
<a href="javascript:card_browser(591)">Koil</a> x2<br />
<a href="javascript:card_browser(683)">Dark <a href="javascript:card_browser(400)">Furok</a></a> x1<br />
<a href="javascript:card_browser(585)">Dark <a href="javascript:card_browser(325)">Ayebaw</a></a> x3<br />
<a href="javascript:card_browser(588)">G<a href="javascript:card_browser(344)">Ora</a>th</a> x1<br />
<br />
Relics~<br />
Tomes of the Great Library x3<br />
<a href="javascript:card_browser(567)">Shadow Bones</a> x3<br />
<a href="javascript:card_browser(575)">Warrada</a>&#39;s Ring x2<br />
<br />
Spells~<br />
Crushing Roots x3<br />
<a href="javascript:card_browser(355)">Shockwave</a> x2<br />
<a href="javascript:card_browser(700)">Vaporize</a> x3<br />
<a href="javascript:card_browser(553)">Corrupt</a> x2<br />
<a href="javascript:card_browser(557)">Maelstrom</a> x2<br />
<a href="javascript:card_browser(555)">Entomb</a> x2<br />
<a href="javascript:card_browser(614)">Deadfall</a> x1<br />
<a href="javascript:card_browser(790)">Beam of Light</a> x2<br />
<a href="javascript:card_browser(554)">Dream Rift</a> x1<br />
<a href="javascript:card_browser(760)">Vim and Vigor</a> x1<br />
<a href="javascript:card_browser(571)">M<a href="javascript:card_browser(344)">Ora</a>g</a>&#39;s Gift x1<br />
<br />
<br />
Total: 43 cards (not-including Magi)<br />
<br />
By:Travis (sivarT)   </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Strategy</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> Okay, Here is the strategy behind the greatest deck ever made.<br />
<br />
First of all, Dark Twins are GODLY. Decide to go first, pull out your entomb, a gorath, and a corrupt. Then Draw 4 more cards, to a starting hand of seven. You might draw a shadow bones, or a shockwave, both good draws. Then entomb shockwave. That way you can play it, and your opponents can not. Depending on the deck your playing, you might want to entomb their power cards, such as Gorgle&#39;s curse, or crushing heat. Then lay down your gorath and any other creatures that you drew, leaving around 12-15 energy left on your mage. Shadow bones the Gorath, which now they cant kill because of the entomb. Then before you draw, drop the corrupt and start laughing as you draw your two cards. Their first creature becomes yours, and all others fall to gorath. Energize for seven every turn, and laught as you use their own spells against them. <br />
<br />
Warrada is a good magi, and she is highly underrated. First of all, starting hands can win the game, so Warrada was my first pick. She probably has one of the best starting hands, Take a Chaos Jile, a Tomes of the Great Library, and Her ring. The ring is powerfull after the first turn, and I will talk about the Tomes a little later. Often with warrada, you want to suicide melee attack, leaving you and your opponent open, so then you basically energize for ten, and you can just search for the little card called maelstrom, also a game winner. <br />
<br />
Card Strategies~ <br />
Creatures: <br />
Dagok- a good all around creature that makes your opponents hate you, especially against cald. And you get to play him for one less if you want.<br />
Gorath- one of the best core creatures, he enslaves all of your opponents stuff. Yay.<br />
Dark Ayebaw- also a game winning card, if you dont need some cards just discard them. If you didnt entomb shockwaves, and you have one in your hand, use it with dark ayebaw.<br />
Koil- The energy can be handy, and its mainly there to reshuffle all your cards into your deck again. More for the Tomes<br />
Chaos Jile- Fun to play with, and can be very bothersome<br />
Rabid Wasperine- a creature that makes your opponents stop their &quot; I just killed you &quot; Dance. you say no, and plop down a five creature for four. Liked that didn&#39;t ya?<br />
<br />
Relics:<br />
Shadow bones- I don&#39;t think I even need to explain this card. Its godly, especially on Jiles and Gorath, and whatever Corrupt takes over, because it becomes core.<br />
Warrada&#39;s Ring- a very powerfull card after the first turn. Just choose whatever you need.<br />
Tomes of the Great Library- One of the staple cards in the deck. Search for anything play it, even out of region stuff (un-entombed shockwave) and the stuff that you need the most. Maelstroms are always help full and so are beam of lights. Also, just laught at your opponents pitifull attemts to discard it, because they cant. And if they manage to steal it, too bad, it gets discarded.<br />
<br />
Spells:<br />
Maelstrom- A very powerfull spell that kills the mage, even if they are sitting on a lot of energy<br />
Corrupt- one of the most powerfull core cards. Especially when you get it as a starting card. Play it when your opponents creature situation is looking grim, and you got that magi in a bag.<br />
Beam of light- a very good utility card that pretty much hits anything you want it too, including those annoying sunburns, or phrups.<br />
Dream Rift- get your creatures back in your deck, and the best part draw 3 cards.<br />
Vaporize- a very nast spell, especially against heavy relic decks. Just say goodbye to all there relics as they scream and say, &quot;That card&#39;s a common??!!???&quot;<br />
Shockwave- very nice spell to kill just about anything you want it too. Entomb it or search for it through the library, and your set. If you cant do either, just dark ayebaw it. <br />
Morag&#39;s Gift- Very good against weenie beater decks like bograth. Shoot one of your creatures that you stole (yes it goes to YOUR hand) and then sit back and add up the energy.<br />
Vim and Vigor- Say there is an annoying greater garganoc in play. Can&#39;t shockwave it, and its just gaining energy. O well, lets move all of that to my mage, and take it over. Thanks for all the enery.<br />
Entomb- a very good spell, that can ruin many decks very easily. Lots of decks have staple spells that always save them. Well not anymore. You can even experiment a little and put your own spells from any region, and then just entomb it so you can play it<br />
Deadfall- IF you used all your corrupts, and they have no creatures, dont fear make them weak. Search for it, or play it from your hand. <br />
Crushing roots- obvious uses, your weak creatures die, mine gain energy. That game was fun.<br />
<br />
Overall this deck wins a lot once my freind and I were playing a multiplayer game, 3v2 and i took out all there magi with one spell, Maelstrom, I searched for it played it, killed all 3 of them, and still had energy to spare. This deck can be a force to reckon with, and it can be easily experimented with. Have fun and don&#39;t make any friends hate you.  </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP" COLSPAN="2"><font class="bfont"> <a href="/magination/decks/decks.php?PHPSESSID=6b84db03bbbbdaba0e935e0d072b04f6">Back to Decks Directory</a> | <A HREF="/magination/decks/decks.php?reviews=32849&PHPSESSID=6b84db03bbbbdaba0e935e0d072b04f6"> Read Reviews </A> | <a href="deckprint.php?deck=32849&PHPSESSID=6b84db03bbbbdaba0e935e0d072b04f6" TARGET="BLANK_"> Printer Friendly</a></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE><a name="review"></a><font class="h2font">In order to review decks you must be a registered member. <A href="/magination/main/join.php?PHPSESSID=6b84db03bbbbdaba0e935e0d072b04f6">Sign up for free!</A></font></td></tr></table></td>
